com.projecttango.unibw.graphmapper.dialog

Class Dialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.projecttango.unibw.graphmapper.dialog.Dialog

  • public class Dialog
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains all user input dialogs as static functions. For example the user can give a hallway a specific name. This class was created by Konstantin Klinger on 26.04.16.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Konstantin Klinger

      • resumeRecordingDialog

        private static void resumeRecordingDialog(GraphmapperActivity contextActivity,
                         ADFPair pair)
        Dialog to ask the user if he want to start the application in viewer or recording state. Viewer state: The user can load an exisiting graph/adf and see his current position at the floor plans Recording state: The user can load an existing graph/adf and resume recording.
        Parameters:
        contextActivity - (context - activity where the dialog displays)
        pair - (selected adf pair to be loaded)
